=====================================
Configuration
=====================================

Configuration of is handled through CMake.
To configure run cmake from the build directory:

cd /path/to/build/dir
cmake \
    -D CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE:STRING="Release" \
    -D TPL_Boost_DIR:PATH=/path/to/boost/install/dir \
    -D TPL_HDF5_DIR:PATH=/path/to/hdf5/install/dir \
    -D TPL_Trilinos_DIR:PATH=/path/to/trilinos/install/dir \
    -D TPL_VTK_DIR:PATH=/path/to/vtk/install/dir \
    -D CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX:PATH=/path/to/install/dir \
    /path/to/source/dir

where /path/to/source/dir is the directory containig this README

You can use the following variables to tell cmake where to find
third party libraries (tipically each of these directories should
contain a "lib" and an "include" subdirectory):

    -D TPL_Boost_DIR:PATH=/path/to/boost/install/dir
    -D TPL_HDF5_DIR:PATH=/path/to/hdf5/install/dir
    -D TPL_Trilinos_DIR:PATH=/path/to/trilinos/install/dir
    -D TPL_VTK_DIR:PATH=/path/to/vtk/install/dir

To specify the type of build you can set the variable CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE
to one of the following:
    Release     compiles with flags -O2 -DNDEBUG
    Debug       compiles with flags -D_GLIBCXX_DEBUG -DDEBUG -g -O0
    Profile     compiles with flags -O2 -pg

To build tests (which can be executed from the build directory
calling "ctest") specify the option:
    -D <ProjectName>_ENABLE_TESTS:BOOL=ON

=====================================
Build
=====================================
To build everything run make from the build directory
cd /path/to/build/dir
make

To build documentation use the 'doc' target:
make doc

CMake generates different targes for every library, executable and test.
they are all included in the target "all" but can be built individually.
To list available targes:
cd /path/to/build/dir
make help

=====================================
Testing
=====================================
To run test:
cd /path/to/build/dir
make
ctest

=====================================
Install
=====================================
cd /path/to/build/dir
make install

